Bloemfontein Celtic and Kaizer Chiefs have both had DStv Premiership fixtures brought forward because of their commitments in African club competition next weekend. Celtic make their debut in the African Confederation Cup against AS Maniema of the Democratic Republic of Congo in Kindu on Sunday, 29 November while Chiefs compete in the African Champions League against Cameroon’s PWD Bamenda away in Limbe the same day Celtic’s scheduled home game against Black Leopards has been moved now to Wednesday, 25 November while Chiefs’ game at Dobsonville against newly promoted Swallows FC will now be played on Tuesday, 24 November. Both re-arranged games will still be screened live on SuperSport. It is expected that the league will also rearrange Celtic and Chiefs’ fixtures for the second leg dates on the weekend of 5-7 December. -SuperSport